          "type": "warning"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Macarons require an oven thermometer. Domestic ovens drift by 20°C or more and the baking window for macarons is narrow. A thermometer is not optional.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Coffee macarons follow the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Italian meringue method",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "Italian meringue method",
                  "termId": "cmpbd4gmf00008gv4748h14tb"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " for stability. The critical step is ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "macaronage",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "macaronage",
                  "termId": "cmp99by26000000v4hvmqwvl2"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": under-folded paste produces cracked shells; over-folded paste produces flat, footless ones. Resting the piped shells until a dry skin forms is what creates the characteristic ",
            "type": "text"
          },
